{"input": "[Neg · actor specification · 2NR] How do I format a shell that argues the affirmative must specify the actor that implements the plan?", "output": "Interpretation – the affirmative must specify the actor that implements the plan.\n\nViolation- They don’t. 1. Ground – the aff doesn’t provide an agent which ought to enact the plan – that strips the neg of agent DAs, process CPs, nuanced K links, and numerous case answers. We’re forced to defend what they’re most prepped on – sanctions good – meaning infinite aff prep causes them to win every round.\n\n2. 1AR shift – the 1AR can re-define normal means and they have authority over what their plan entails. We’re forced to get unverifiable cross-x agreements and pre-emptively not read most of our offense because the 1AR can moot it, and the 2NR can’t restart.", "category": "Theory", "mode": "normal"}
